        "text_dHHdj7": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>At <strong>Environmental Biotech</strong>, we specialize in cutting-edge <strong>bioremediation technology</strong>—a natural and eco-friendly solution that uses live vegetative bacteria to break down grease, sugars, and organic waste that commonly clog <a href=\"https://environmentalbiotech.ca/pages/commercial-drainage-overview\" title=\"https://environmentalbiotech.ca/pages/commercial-drainage-overview\">commercial drainage systems</a>. Unlike many products on the market that rely on dormant spore-based bacteria, our live bacteria get to work immediately, delivering fast and effective results. Because they are non-toxic, non-pathogenic, and fully active upon application, our solutions offer a superior, environmentally responsible alternative to traditional drain maintenance.</p><p>In addition to bioremediation, <strong>Environmental Biotech</strong> manufactures a full line of <strong>EPA-registered disinfectants</strong>. These high-performance products are formulated to eliminate harmful pathogens, including viruses, bacteria, and fungi. Whether you're safeguarding your home, business, or workplace, our disinfectants provide powerful protection against foodborne illnesses and contagious diseases—helping you maintain a cleaner, healthier environment for your family, customers, and employees.</p>"
          }
        }
